The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, July 14: Fiat India today slashed the price of its flagship model Palio by Rs 22,000. The reduced price for the three models of the Palio comes into immediate effect in Mumbai. Prices will be reduced in other cities, including Calcutta, Delhi and Bangalore, over the next few days. After the price slash, the top-end 1.2-litre Palio ELX will be available at Rs 4.15 lakh. The 1.2-litre Palio NV EL MS will cost Rs 3,64,364 and the 1.2-litre NV EL PS will be priced at Rs 3,92,053.

 New Delhi, July 14: Tata Coffee has bid for six estates of Tata Tea in south India for Rs 55 crore, the company has informed the Bombay Stock Exchange. The transaction would be subject to necessary approvals. 

 Mumbai, July 14: Rajeev Batra, former chief architect for IT and technology at Bharti Tele-Ventures, has joined Anil Dhirubhai Ambani Enterprises as vice- president for IT and technology.

 New Delhi, July 14: India will provide a Rs 1,984-crore assistance package to Bhutan for its sixth five year plan ending 2007.

 New Delhi, July 14: The government is planning to bring non-banking finance companies under the purview of the Companies Act as part of its efforts to regulate their functioning, said company affairs minister P.C. Gupta.




